  <h2>Who it is for</h2>
  <p>
    Students who intend to sit entrance examinations for MA or PhD programs in
    economics, and who want preparation that takes the mathematics seriously. The
    program assumes an undergraduate background in economics; gaps in mathematics
    are expected and addressed, not assumed away.
  </p>

  <h2>What we cover</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Microeconomics</strong> — consumer and producer theory, choice under
      uncertainty, general equilibrium, and game theory, at examination depth.</li>
    <li><strong>Mathematics</strong> — the real analysis, linear algebra, and
      optimisation these examinations actually test.</li>
    <li><strong>Statistics</strong> — probability, distributions, estimation, and
      inference.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <p>
    Live online sessions, with problem-solving at the centre of every meeting.
    Between sessions you work through assigned problems; in sessions, solutions are
    built from scratch on the board, with full working. Doubts are discussed in the
    community forum, where they benefit everyone.
  </p>

  <h2>Schedule and fees</h2>
  <p>
    Dates, schedule, and fees for the current cohort are published on the
    <a href="/announcements/">announcements page</a> when applications open, and
    confirmed by email after you register interest.
  </p>

  <h2>Apply or ask</h2>
  <p>
    To apply, or to ask whether the program fits where you are, write to us — see
    the <a href="/about/#contact">contact details</a>. There is no harm in asking
    early; we would rather help you decide honestly than enrol you into the wrong
    thing.
  </p>
</Layout>
